nosto_cart.collection: | Plexia Black | Stainless Steel Bracelet | Black Dial |
nosto_cart.description:
Known worldwide for its unique statement pieces, Storm is a British brand founded in London in 1989. From its creation, the brand specialised in watch design but has since branched out into other accessories as well. Watches however remain at the forefront of the brand’s portfolio. After more than 30 years, Storm has continued to amaze and challenge with its imaginative silhouettes and designs. The brand places the focus on individuality and tries to push the boundaries of what was previously possible with every new model. 

Core Features of a Storm Watch: 

  • Storm watches are inspired not only by trends but by the world in general. 
  • Due to the brand’s love for sculptural silhouettes, each Storm model is instantly recognisable 
  • A driving force behind each design is the innovative use of technology and materials.
  • All Storm watches are powered by a quartz mechanism.

Model Specifications: 47450/BK

  • This model is a part of Storm's Plexia collection.
  • The watch’s bangle-style bracelet and rectangle case are made of stainless steel and have a brushed finish. The case features transparent acrylic elements. 
  • Protecting the black dial is a mineral crystal. 
  • The watch is splash-resistant and should not come in contact with water.

page_title: Alsta Nautoscaph Superautomatic 1970 Re-Edition (300m) Black Dial / SUPERAUTOMATIC-BRACELET - First Class Watches™
meta_description: Alsta SUPERAUTOMATIC-BRACELET - [[DELIVERY_INSTOCK]]. Alsta has a long history in diver&rsquo;s watches and is most famous for its timepiece which was featured on Richard Dreyfuss&rsquo; wrist in the movie Jaws. The brand rose to&nbsp;popularity throughout the 60s and 70s and recently made its grand return in 2014. The Nautoscaph Superautomatic has now been re-issued as a limited edition model. Though Alsta has tried to preserve the original&nbsp;design of the &quot;Jaws&quot; watch, the model has been re-made using modern materials and&nbsp;technologies. Core Features of Alsta Watches: Alsta watches are primarily powered by&nbsp;automatic mechanical movements.&nbsp; Encasing the dial on each watch is a&nbsp;sapphire crystal.&nbsp; For added practicality, Alsta watches feature&nbsp;luminescent indices and hands.&nbsp; Each Alsta watch is&nbsp;water resistant up to at least 300 metres (30 bar).&nbsp; Model Specifications:&nbsp;SUPERAUTOMATIC-BRACELET The&nbsp;case and bracelet are made of satin-finished&nbsp;stainless steel&nbsp;and measures 38&nbsp;mm in diameter.&nbsp; The&nbsp;dial is black&nbsp;and&nbsp;features&nbsp;luminescent hands and indices. The luminescence is&nbsp;C3 Super-LumiNova. The&nbsp;stainless steel porthole bracelet&nbsp;secures the watch. The dial is encased by&nbsp;a sapphire crystal. Functions of the watch include a screw-in crown,&nbsp;a&nbsp;date, hours, minutes and seconds.&nbsp; Water-resistant up to 300 metres or 30 bars. Movement Type -&nbsp;Automatic. Calibre -&nbsp;Seiko NH35A Limited to only 1975&nbsp;pieces. . Official Alsta UK retailer. The Alsta SUPERAUTOMATIC-BRACELET comes with free delivery, 2 year guarantee, 30 day returns and box.

product_reviews.title: Review Title
product_reviews.text: Alsta Nautoscaphe, the watch arrived in a generic cardboard box and within was the case for the Alsta which is a plastic travel case which was a little disappointing, on opening the case I was pleased to find a very good looking and well built watch (with only one gripe), the bracelet is nicer than I expected however the safety clasp has very little grip and having experience with this type of clasp on a Tag Heuer expect this to require repair or replacement in the near future, and it will need a light squeeze with pliers to get the detent to latch with any force. The dial is beautiful and the finish is very good, the watch is heavier than expected for its size but I like that bit of heft with the watch. The dial is small but the large cushion type case makes the watch look bigger on the wrist. Overall I am happy with the watch but for the money an ETA movement would make the watch a little more special.

product_reviews.products_name: Alsta Nautoscaph Superautomatic 1970 Re-Edition (300m) Black Dial / Stainless Steel SUPERAUTOMATIC-BRACELET

product_reviews.text: This is my first purchase from First Class Watches and the service I received was fantastic. I ordered the Alsta ‘Jaws’ and it arrived within 2 days.  It’s a lovely vintage looking watch which I can’t fault.

product_reviews.name: Stephen
product_reviews.products_name: Alsta Nautoscaph Superautomatic 1970 Re-Edition (300m) Black Dial / Stainless Steel SUPERAUTOMATIC-BRACELET
product_reviews.title: Review Title
product_reviews.text: I would buy from this company again. Just purchased the Alsta Nautoscaph ‘Jaws’ watch. Very pleased with it. Apparently they are selling out quickly in other countries due to the limited amount made. I got number 421 of 1975. The watch itself is solid, well made, stunning to look at and comfortable. I’ve always wanted one. Initially I was concerned about buying over the internet but the payment system is secure with the watch arriving well packaged and surprisingly quick. In addition, the communication regarding the delivery was excellent. Very happy customer.

product_reviews.title: Review Title
product_reviews.text: As an avid collector of watches, I must admit I've never bought from First Class Watches before. However, the watch I wanted was not available on the manufacture's site as it is a limited edition, so when I stumbled across it on the First Class Watch site I was blown away and had to have it.  Even in the middle of this crazy pandemic, the watch arrived the following day. I love the watch and only 1975 are being made - luckily, and for some crazy reason, mine is number 5!  ...How they ended up with such a low production number I've no idea. But I'm super grateful.  ...First Class Watches - you did me proud!  I'll be back.

product_info.name: Alsta Nautoscaph Superautomatic 1970 Re-Edition (300m) Black Dial / Stainless Steel SUPERAUTOMATIC-BRACELET
product_info.collection: Nautoscaph Superautomatic 1970 Re-Edition (300m) Black Dial / Stainless Steel
product_info.description:
Alsta has a long history in diver’s watches and is most famous for its timepiece which was featured on Richard Dreyfuss’ wrist in the movie Jaws. The brand rose to popularity throughout the 60s and 70s and recently made its grand return in 2014. The Nautoscaph Superautomatic has now been re-issued as a limited edition model. Though Alsta has tried to preserve the original design of the "Jaws" watch, the model has been re-made using modern materials and technologies.

Core Features of Alsta Watches:

  • Alsta watches are primarily powered by automatic mechanical movements. 
  • Encasing the dial on each watch is a sapphire crystal. 
  • For added practicality, Alsta watches feature luminescent indices and hands. 
  • Each Alsta watch is water resistant up to at least 300 metres (30 bar). 

Model Specifications: SUPERAUTOMATIC-BRACELET

  • The case and bracelet are made of satin-finished stainless steel and measures 38 mm in diameter. 
  • The dial is black and features luminescent hands and indices. The luminescence is C3 Super-LumiNova.
  • The stainless steel porthole bracelet secures the watch.
  • The dial is encased by a sapphire crystal.
  • Functions of the watch include a screw-in crown, a date, hours, minutes and seconds. 
  • Water-resistant up to 300 metres or 30 bars.
  • Movement Type - Automatic.
  • Calibre - Seiko NH35A
  • Limited to only 1975 pieces.
